American Airlines flies direct to Miami. Other options include a variety of destinations via Panama, and LAN and TACA also fly to Santa Cruz. Gol Airlines and Aerolineas Argentinas also offer flights to São Paulo and Buenos Aires, respectively.

To get into downtown Santa Cruz from the airport you have two options. The first is to take a taxi that will charge you approximately Bs. 60  (~$9). This is probably the easiest and most comfortable way to get into town, but if you are on a tight budget the second option is a "micro" or mini-bus that waits outside the front doors of the airport that leaves every 20 minutes, the fare for the bus is only 6bs (~$.90). This bus follows the Cristo Redentor Avenue and then along the First Ring. To get to the main plaza, ask the driver to let you off at Libertad and Primer Anillo (First Ring). From there, it is about about a seven block walk.

